Content:
If you are running firefox, you can use the userContent.css file to apply a custom style to visited links on HN to make them do anything you want.<p>Something like this in your userContent.css file:<p><pre><code>  @-moz-document url-prefix(https://news.ycombinator.com/) {
      a:visited { color: #ffffff !important; }
  }
</code></pre>
Would make all visited links on HN pure white (not likely the color you want, substitute your preferred &quot;grey&quot; RGB color for the &quot;ffffff&quot; color above).<p>Note, you do have to restart firefox to make changes in userContent.css become effective.
